TITLE: Efficient Highcharts Configuration Using Object Literals in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of a properly written Highcharts configuration using JavaScript object literals. This approach is more concise and readable than using verbose object creation syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/getting-started/how-to-set-options.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Good code:
const options = {
    chart: {
        type: 'bar'
    },
    series: [{
        name: 'Jane',
        data: [1, 0, 4]
    }]
};
```

