TITLE: Customizing Axis Labels in Highcharts JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to customize axis labels in Highcharts by adding a '%' symbol to y-axis labels using either a format string or a formatter function. Dependencies include Highcharts library and correct initialization of the chart object. The formatter function directly modifies the label output based on the axis value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/chart-concepts/axes.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
yAxis: {
    labels: {
        format: '{value}%',''// provides the same result as:
        formatter: function() {
            return this.value + ' %';
        }
    },
},
```

