TITLE: Defining Dashboard Components
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript array defines the components to be included in the dashboard. Each component specifies its `type`, `renderTo` (cell ID), and options.  The first component is an HTML element (a heading), rendered in `dashboard-col-0`, while the second is a Highcharts chart, rendered in `dashboard-col-1`, with a simple series containing sample data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/dashboards/your-first-dashboard.md#2025-04-16_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
components: [{
    type: 'HTML',
    renderTo: 'dashboard-col-0',
    elements: [
        {
            tagName: 'h1',
            textContent: 'Your first dashboard'
        }
    ]
}, {
    renderTo: 'dashboard-col-1',
    type: 'Highcharts',
    chartOptions: {
        series: [{
            data: [1, 2, 3, 4]
        }]
    }
}]
```

