DESCRIPTION: This snippet features a configuration example for synchronized Highcharts components using a common CSV data connector. It enables visibility, highlight, and extremes sync types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/dashboards/synchronize-components.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
Dashboards.board('container', {
  dataPool: {
      connectors: [{
          id: 'Vitamin',
          type: 'CSV',
          options: {
              csv: `Food,Vitamin A,Iron
              Beef Liver,6421,6.5
              Lamb Liver,2122,6.5
              Cod Liver Oil,1350,0.9
              Mackerel,388,1
              Tuna,214,0.6`,
          },
      }]
  },
  components: [{
      connector: {
          id: 'Vitamin'
      },
      sync: {
          visibility: true,
          highlight: true,
          extremes: true
      },
      renderTo: 'dashboard-col-0',
      type: 'Highcharts'
  }, {
      renderTo: 'dashboard-col-1',
      connector: {
          id: 'Vitamin'
      },
      sync: {
          visibility: true,
          highlight: true,
          extremes: true
      },
      type: 'Highcharts'
  }]
});
```

