TITLE: Creating a Custom Placement Strategy in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to define a custom word placement strategy called `randomPlacement`. This strategy computes random positions for words and is integrated by setting it to the `placementStrategy` property of a Highcharts wordcloud series.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/chart-and-series-types/word-cloud-series.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
var randomPlacement = function randomPlacement(point, options) {
  var field = options.field,
    r = options.rotation;
  return {
    x: getRandomPosition(field.width) - (field.width / 2),
    y: getRandomPosition(field.height) - (field.height / 2),
   rotation: getRotation(r.orientations, r.from, r.to)
  };
};
```

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
Highcharts.seriesTypes.wordcloud.prototype.placementStrategy.random= randomPlacement;
```

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
Highcharts.chart(..., {
  series: [{
    type: 'wordcloud',
    placementStrategy: 'random'
  }]
});
```

