TITLE: Implementing Linear Regression with Multiple Zones in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Code snippet showing how to calculate linear regression with multiple zone lines. The code generates data points for five different lines representing different percentage zones of the main regression line.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/stock/custom-technical-indicators.md#2025-04-16_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var zoneDistance = this.options.params.zoneDistance / 100;

// Calculate linear regression:
for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
  x = xData[i];
  y = alpha * x + beta;

  // Prepare arrays required for getValues() method
  linearData[i] = [x, y * (1 - 2 * zoneDistance), y * (1 - zoneDistance), y, y * (1 + zoneDistance), y * (1 + 2 * zoneDistance)];
  linearXData[i] = x;
  linearYData[i] = [y * (1 - 2 * zoneDistance), y * (1 - zoneDistance), y, y * (1 + zoneDistance), y * (1 + 2 * zoneDistance)];
}

return {
  xData: linearXData,
  yData: linearYData,
  values: linearData
};
```

