TITLE: Creating Labels for Fibonacci Retracement Levels in Highcharts
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet creates labels for each Fibonacci retracement level in Highcharts. It iterates through the retracement levels, creates a label object with the level value as text, and configures its position and style. The label is positioned at point p1, which is assumed to be created with the point function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/advanced-chart-features/annotations-and-fibonacci-retracements.md#2025-04-16_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js
const labels = [];

levels.forEach(function (level, i) {
    const retracement = y2 - diff * level,
        p1 = point(x1, retracement),
        p2 = point(x2, retracement);

    labels.push({
        point: p1,
        text: level.toString(),
        allowOverlap: true,
        align: 'right',
        y: 0,
        backgroundColor: 'none',
        verticalAlign: 'middle',
        shape: 'rect',
        borderWidth: 0,
        style: {
            color: 'grey'
        }
    });
});
```
