DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the recommended pattern for defining classes and their associated types in TypeScript within the Highcharts project. It combines the class implementation with a namespace containing related interfaces, ensuring clear separation and accessibility of both implementation and types. This pattern is beneficial when types are exclusively tied to a specific class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/ts/README.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
"class MyClass {
    /* properties and functions using MyClass.MyType */
    private myProperty?: MyClass.MyType;
    public myFunction(arg: MyClass.MyType) {
        /* ... */
    }
}
namespace MyClass {
    export interface MyType {
        /* ... */
    }
}
export default MyClass; // allows access to both, class implementation and types"
```

