TITLE: Mapping Audio Parameters to Functions in Highcharts
DESCRIPTION: Example of mapping volume and other audio parameters using a function that determines volume based on point color. The function receives a context object with time, point, and value data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/highcharts/highcharts/blob/master/docs/sonification/advanced-mapping.md#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
mapping: {
    // Volume is 0.8 for red points, 0.3 for all other points
    volume: (context) => {
        const point = context.point || {};
        return point.color === 'red' ? 0.8 : 0.3;
    },
    pan: 0,
    noteDuration: 300,
    pitch: 'a3'
}
```

